OMI-GRAPH:
  The authoritative representation of all system state.

BOM:
  Byte Order Mark used as a clock principle: each tick is an endian
  reinterpretation boundary.

CONS:
  A stable adjacency binding between graph nodes.

NULL field:
  Memory interpreted as graph nodes before stable adjacency emerges.

Polyform:
  A reversible external projection of graph state, such as Braille, Aegean, or
  mixed-base encoding.
